\subsubsection{Conversion System}

Because of the new EP costs, the Ranks of current Philosophers may not
be simply changed to the same Rank in the new skill, as low Ranked
characters will not have paid enough EP, and high Ranked ones have
paid too much.  The simplest solution is to convert a Philosopher's
Ranks across but modify the number of ``field points'' gained.  Find
the characters present Rank on the table below.  The ``field points''
column is the number of points that they are given in one lump to
spend on Realms, Major Fields, etc, at the normal rate.  They should
spend these points so as to attempt to cover the same fields as they
already had, wherever possible.  The ``max.  realms'' column is the
maximum number of Realms that they may purchase.  Once converted, a
character may purchase a number of extra point (at 700 EP each) up to
the number shown in the ``extra points'' column with no time
expenditure.  The number that may be purchased should be noted down as
these may be bought st any time in the future and need not be
purchased at the time of conversion.  The only Rank for which this
system does not work is Rank 0.  Philosophers who have this skill at
Rank 0, receive the same Rank in the new skill but must pay 1000 extra
ep. before they can increase their Rank.

{\fontsize{7pt}{8}\selectfont
\begin{tabular}{cccc}
		& \textbf{Field} & \textbf{Max.} & \textbf{Extra} \\
\textbf{Rank}	& \textbf{Points}& \textbf{Realms} & \textbf{Points} \\
0*		& 8		& 1		& 0 \\
1		& 10		& 1		& 1 \\
2		& 12		& 1		& 2 \\
3		& 13		& 1		& 4 \\
4		& 21		& 2		& 5 \\
5		& 30		& 2		& 3 \\
6		& 37		& 2		& 1 \\
7		& 51		& 3		& 0 \\
8		& 63		& 3		& 0 \\ 
9		& 76		& 3		& 0 \\
10		& 104		& 4		& 0 \\
\end{tabular}}

*must pay 1000 extra ep before advancing further.
